column5: Unfortunately that Grandma might be one of the last of her kind... https://bluefishcanada.ca/the-death-of-the-st-lawrence-musky-fishery/ Interesting opinion by John Anderson that long line trolling is contributing to their decline...as opposed to casting
Does it say what the girth was.   	nice fish.

While mine only goes to 30 pounds , those Chantillion scales in the picture can be certified for IGFA records, at least at one time.  Might be a good idea to get it certified in world record waters https://www.chatillon-scales.com/products/handheld-scales/in-series-fish-and-game-linear-handheld-scales
Wow, that's a monster muskie Cullen caught! Must've been one heck of a fight. Was he using one of his custom lures?

sad to have long line trolling a bullcrap issue. blaming use of planer boards. obviously that statement is biased and un-educated. lets just blame using hooks and boats with motors.yes theres been issues but to construe tactics,lets just ban fishfinders also.
